
[1]criticism

   CRITICISM, n.

   1. The art of judging with propriety of the beauties and faults of a
   literary performance, or of any production in the fine arts; as the
   rules of criticism.

   2. The act of judging on the merit of a performance; animadversion;
   remark on beauties and faults; critical observation, verbal or written.
   We say, the authors criticisms are candid, or they are severe.
